        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="10">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury and/or property damage, park the vehicle on a level surface and
                        chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two parking brake lever shroud mounting screws located at the base and inside
                    the cup holder
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190901">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190902">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0190901" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190901.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                             scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Parking Brake and Cup Holder Shroud</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. CUP HOLDER</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SHORT BRAKE RELEASE ASSEMBLY (MANUAL TRANSMISSIONS)</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. TALL BRAKE RELEASE ASSEMBLY (AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSIONS)</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. SHROUD MOUNTING SCREW</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0190902" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190902.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Brake and Shroud, Top View (Tall Brake Assembly Shown)</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. BRAKE HANDLE ASSEMBLY SHROUD</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SHROUD MOUNTING SCEW (IN BOTTOM OF CUP HOLDER)</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shroud.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the the parking brake light harness connector
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190903">(Figure 3)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0190903" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190903.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. Harness Connector Disconnect</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. SHROUD MOUNTING HOLE (CUP HOLDER)</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. PARKING BRAKE HANDLE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move the park brake lever to the released position. (Cable tension of 500 lbs could
                    cause injury).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 4 mounting fasteners, (3 nuts and 1 bolt, short brake assembly) and (4 bolts,
                    tall brake assembly) located at the parking brake base plate
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190904">(Figure 4)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0190904" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190904.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4. Mounting Fastener Removal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. MOUNTING STUD AND NUT OR BOLT</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the parking brake lever from the base plate and position it on its side to gain
                    access to the parking brake cable
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190905">(Figure 5)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0190905" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190905.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5. Parking Brake Cable Access</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. CABLE HOUSING END ATTACHMENT FOR MANUAL TRANSMISSIONS</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. PARKING BRAKE CONTROL MOUNTING STUDS FOR MANUAL TRANSMISSION OR BOLTS FOR AUTOMATIC
                            TRANSMISSION
                        </callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">To maintain tension on cable use small vice grip to hold cable in place
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0190906">(Figure 6)</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0190906" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190906.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                                 scalefitheight="272px"/>
                        <caption>Figure 6. Securing Brake Cable</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. CABLE HOUSING ATTACHMENT</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cotter pin and washer from the pivot pin
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190907">(Figure 7)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0190907" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190907.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7. Cotter Pin Removal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. PIVOT PIN</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. COTTER PIN</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0190908" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190908.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                             scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8. Pivot Pin Removal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. PIVOT PIN</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pivot yoke
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190908">(Figure 8)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the parking brake cable from the yoke
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190909">(Figure 9)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0190909" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190909.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                             scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9. Disconnect Parking Brake Cable From Yoke</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. CABLE END ATTACHMENT</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. PARKING BRAKE CABLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. PIVOT YOKE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0190910" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0190910.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                             scalefitheight="352px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10. Tall Brake Release Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. PIVOT YOKE ARM</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. PIVOT PIN LOCATION</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. PIVOT YOKE</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. PARKING BRAKE CABLE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. BRAKE RELEASE MECHANISM</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. PARK BRAKE RELEASE HANDLE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">Tall Parking Brake Lever, Part Number 3541522C6, Only:</emph>
                    Disconnect the cable housing from the parking brake lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The new short parking brake lever, Part Number 3541521C6, will be supplied with a mounting
                        base plate. Remove and discard the base plate.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the parking brake cable to the pivot yoke and assemble to the new lever, by
                    installing the pivot pin, washer and cotter pin
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190907">(Figure 7</hotlnk>and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0190908">Figure 8).</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">Tall Parking Brake Lever, Part Number 3541522C6, Only:</emph>Connect the parking
                    brake cable housing to the new lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Continue installing the new parking brake lever by following Steps 1 to 7 in reverse
                    order.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Retorque fasteners to 72-96 in-lbs (8-11 Nm)</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Removed parts are to be destroyed and disposed of locally.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
